President Muhammadu Buhari Monday afternoon spoke to Ban Ki-Moon over the phone and said Nigeria was in full appreciation to the former United Nations Secretary General for his commitment towards the progress and socio-economic development of Nigeria. President Buhari in a statement by his media aide, Garba Shehu, reiterated his long-standing respect and admiration for the two-time UN Scribe and thanked him for initiating the call. Ban Ki-Moon commended the President for his handling of security and related challenges facing the country. He expressed appreciation for the support of two prominent citizens of Nigeria-Professor Ibrahim Gambari, Presidentâ€™s Chief of Staff and one-time UN Undersecretary General and Mrs Amina Mohammed, the current Deputy Secretary General, saying that they are among the best he had ever worked with.